radiographic_examinations.findings: No evidence of infarction, hemorrhage, edema, or mass. There is a large opercular arachnoid cyst, measuring approximately 58 x 34 mm. Mucosal retention cysts of the maxillary sinuses bilaterally. The vessels of the circle of Willis and their principal intracranial branches appear normal without stenosis, occlusion, or aneurysm greater than 3 mm. Carotid and vertebral arteries and their major branches appear normal without evidence of stenosis or occlusion. The visualized portion of the lungs are clear.
